---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Governance Master Project — Structure Map"
  description="The central documents and decision maps of the AI Governance Master Project. Start here if you want to understand how the system is structured."
>
  <section class="section-shell">

    <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">AI Governance Master Project</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-[1.6rem] md:text-[2rem] font-semibold">Structure Map</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">
        This project is organized to help you understand complex systems without getting lost.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">
        The <strong style="color:var(--color-text-primary)">Apex Files</strong> show the overall structure — the big picture. The <strong style="color:var(--color-text-primary)">Governance Trees</strong> then break that down further, showing how decisions are made and how authority moves.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">
        You can start anywhere. If you're unsure, begin with the Apex Files and move into the Governance Trees as needed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="apex-block veil-panel mb-8">
      <p class="eyebrow">Master Project Apex Files</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-[1.2rem] font-semibold">The big picture.</h2>
      <div class="apex-grid mt-6">
        <div class="apex-body">
          <p>The Apex Files are the central documents of this project.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">They bring everything together in one place and show how the system is structured. If you're not sure where to start, this is a good entry point.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">You don't need to understand everything at once. These files are here to help you see the big picture first, and then explore at your own pace.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="apex-aside">
          <div class="apex-card">
            <p class="apex-card-label">For people navigating systems</p>
            <p class="mt-2">This file helps you get oriented. You don't need prior knowledge. Start here and follow what's relevant to you.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apex-card mt-3">
            <p class="apex-card-label">For researchers and analysts</p>
            <p class="mt-2">This document defines the system architecture at a high level. It shows how components relate and interact, and where to look for traceability.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tree-section veil-panel mb-8">
      <p class="eyebrow">Governance Trees</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-[1.2rem] font-semibold">How decisions actually work inside that picture.</h2>
      <div class="apex-grid mt-5 mb-8">
        <div class="apex-body">
          <p>Governance Trees show how decisions are made in a system.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">They show who has authority, how rules are applied, and where actions come from. If you've ever felt blocked or confused by a system, this helps make that structure visible.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">You don't need to read everything — just follow what's relevant to your situation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="apex-aside">
          <div class="apex-card">
            <p class="apex-card-label">For people navigating institutions</p>
            <p class="mt-2">This helps you understand what's shaping your situation. It shows where decisions come from. It can help you see where change is possible — and where it isn't.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="apex-card mt-3">
            <p class="apex-card-label">For researchers and system thinkers</p>
            <p class="mt-2">This models decision pathways and authority distribution. It helps analyze how governance operates in practice and where controls attach.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Research, Method &amp; Governance Infrastructure</p>
      <div id="governance-tree-mount"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tree-section veil-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Skill Ecosystem</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 mb-2 text-[1.2rem] font-semibold">Bounded AI Agent Governance</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 text-sm" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Fourteen operational constitutions that govern how AI agents work within this practice. Each skill has a defined role, defined limits, and a clear trigger. The philosopher skill is the entry point — it routes everything else.</p>
      <div id="skill-tree-mount"></div>
    </div>

  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Layout ── */
.tree-section { width: 100%; }
.apex-block { width: 100%; }
.tree { padding: 0.25rem 0; }

/* ── Apex grid ── */
.apex-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
}
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .apex-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
}
.apex-body {
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}
.apex-body p strong { color: var(--color-text-primary); }
.apex-aside { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.apex-card {
  padding: 12px 16px;
  background: var(--color-background-tertiary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  border: 0.5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary);
  font-size: 13px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}
.apex-card-label {
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: 2px;
}

/* ── Branch (parent) row ── */
.branch-node { position: relative; margin-bottom: 2px; }
.branch-row {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
  padding: 7px 10px; border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.12s;
  border: 0.5px solid transparent;
}
.branch-row:hover { background: var(--color-background-secondary); border-color: var(--color-border-tertiary); }

/* ── Leaf (child) row ── */
.leaf-node { position: relative; }
.leaf-row {
  display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px;
  padding: 5px 10px 5px 0; border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.12s;
  border: 0.5px solid transparent;
}
.leaf-row:hover { background: var(--color-background-secondary); border-color: var(--color-border-tertiary); }

/* ── Toggle ── */
.toggle {
  flex-shrink: 0; width: 18px; height: 18px;
  border-radius: 4px; border: 0.5px solid var(--color-border-secondary);
  background: var(--color-background-secondary);
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; user-select: none;
  transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
}
.toggle.open { background: var(--color-background-info); color: var(--color-text-info); border-color: var(--color-border-info); }

/* ── Arborescence: children container with vertical spine ── */
.children {
  position: relative;
  margin-left: 22px;
  padding-left: 20px;
  border-left: 1.5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary);
  overflow: hidden;
  max-height: 0;
  transition: max-height 0.35s ease;
}
.children.open { max-height: 5000px; }

/* Horizontal connector from spine to each leaf */
.leaf-node::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: -20px;
  top: 13px;
  width: 14px;
  height: 1.5px;
  background: var(--color-border-tertiary);
}
/* Last child: clip the vertical spine below it */
.leaf-node:last-child { position: relative; }
.leaf-node:last-child::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: -22px;
  top: 14px;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 3px;
  background: var(--color-background-primary, #fff);
}

/* ── Labels ── */
.label-wrap { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
.branch-tag {
  display: inline-block; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600;
  padding: 1px 8px; border-radius: 20px; margin-bottom: 3px;
  line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0.02em; text-transform: uppercase;
}
.tag-research { background: #EEEDFE; color: #3C3489; }
.tag-method   { background: #E1F5EE; color: #085041; }
.tag-infra    { background: #FAEEDA; color: #633806; }

.branch-title {
  font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);
}
.node-title {
  font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-text-primary);
  line-height: 1.4;
}
.node-sub {
  font-size: 11px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-top: 2px;
  line-height: 1.4;
}

/* ── Abstract panel ── */
.abstract-panel {
  margin: 3px 0 8px 0; padding: 10px 14px;
  background: var(--color-background-secondary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border-secondary);
  font-size: 12px; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;
  display: none;
}
.abstract-panel.open { display: block; }
.panel-title {
  font-size: 11.5px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary);
  margin-bottom: 6px; line-height: 1.5;
}
.tags-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px; margin-top: 8px; }
.tag-pill {
  font-size: 10px; padding: 1px 7px; border-radius: 20px;
  background: var(--color-background-tertiary); color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  border: 0.5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary);
}

/* ── Skill badges ── */
.badge {
  display: inline-block; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600;
  padding: 1px 8px; border-radius: 20px; margin-bottom: 3px;
  line-height: 1.6; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}
.b-research { background: #EEEDFE; color: #3C3489; }
.b-write    { background: #E1F5EE; color: #085041; }
.b-strat    { background: #FAEEDA; color: #633806; }
.b-orch     { background: #FAECE7; color: #993C1D; }
.b-arch     { background: #E6F1FB; color: #0C447C; }
</style>

<script>
// @ts-nocheck
// ── Governance Tree ──────────────────────────────────────────────
const GOV_DATA = [
