        label:"Cross-System Sequential Audit",
        sub:"Three-Agent Recursive Evaluation · One Auditable Event",
        full:"Cross-System Sequential Audit: Three-Agent Recursive Evaluation of Governance Framework Integrity",
        abstract:"Three AI agents evaluate the same governance framework in sequence: Agatha (ChatGPT) performs first-order audit, Gemini performs second-order evaluation, Claude evaluates Gemini. Three agents, three passes, recursive depth collapsing into a single auditable governance event.",
        tags:["three-agent audit","meta-evaluation","cross-system","recursive depth","sequential"] },
      { id:"shadow",
        label:"Adversarial Inversion Protocol",
        sub:"Red-Team · Institutional Capture and Legitimacy Theater",
        full:"Adversarial Inversion Protocol: Stress Testing Governance Controls Against Institutional Capture and Legitimacy Theater",
        abstract:"Systematic adversarial inversion of every governance principle. Does not abolish governance language — colonizes it. Tests whether each control survives institutional co-optation or collapses into legitimacy theater under adversarial pressure.",
        tags:["adversarial inversion","red team","legitimacy theater","institutional capture","co-optation"] },
      { id:"scripto",
        label:"Automated Pipeline Implementation",
        sub:"Method · Scripted Execution Protocol and Recursive Paper-Builder",
        full:"Automated Recursive Governance: Pipeline Implementation and Scripted Execution Protocol",
        abstract:"The scripted automation test implementation of the RDAIG method. Applies the recursive deterministic governance pipeline to automated paper-building workflows, testing whether the method holds under scripted conditions. Produces recursive analysis memos, evidence hierarchy notes, control registers, disclosure language, and reviewer-pressure scaffolds.",
        tags:["scripted automation","pipeline implementation","paper-builder","RDAIG","recursive scaffolding"] },
    ]
  },
  {
    id: "infra", label: "Governance Infrastructure", tag: "infra", tagClass: "tag-infra", children: [
